{{ESC National Year | Year = 2002 | Country = Austria | Preselection = Song.Null.Zwei | Preselection date = 1 March 2002 | Entrant = [[Manuel Ortega (singer)|Manuel Ortega]] | Song = [[Say A Word]] | Final result = 18th, 26 points | Prev = 2000 | Next = 2003 }} '''Austria''' selected its entrant for the '''Eurovision Song Contest 2002''' in [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]] by holding a national final, the first time since [[Austria in the Eurovision Song Contest 1994|1994]] that a national final was held. Song.Null.Zwei ({{lang-en|Song '02}}) contained 10 participants competing to sing for Austria.
The winner of the contest was [[Manuel Ortega (singer)|Manuel Ortega]] with the song "[[Say A Word]]", and subsequently went on to represent Austria in Tallinn.
==Song.Null.Zwei== The contest was held on 1 March 2002 at the [[ORF (broadcaster)|ORF]] TV Studios in Vienna, hosted by [[Andi Knoll]]. The winner was chosen by a mixture of televoting, SMS voting and an internet jury of 2002 people.
