[[File:Church of the Holy Saviour - Prizren.jpg|thumb|Ruins of the church after the [[2004 unrest in Kosovo]].]]

The '''Church of the Holy Saviour''' ({{lang-sr|Црква Светог Спаса / Crkva Svetog Spasa}}, {{lang-al|Kisha e Shën Spasit}}) is a [[Serbian Orthodox church]] located in [[Prizren]], Kosovo, built around 1330.

The church was declared a [[Monuments of Culture of Exceptional Importance (Serbia)|Monument of Culture of Exceptional Importance]] in 1990, and it is protected by the [[Republic of Serbia]].<ref>[http://spomenicikulture.mi.sanu.ac.rs/spomenik.php?id=333 Споменици културе у Србији - ''Црква светог Спаса'']</ref> It was heavily damaged by a Kosovo Albanian mob during the [[2004 unrest in Kosovo]].<ref>[http://www.spc.rs/Vesti-2004/03/18-3-04_l04.html News from Kosovo and Metohija]{{dead link|date=August 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} {{sr icon}}</ref>

