{{Politics of Serbia and Montenegro}}
{{No footnotes|date=February 2008}}
The '''Constitutional Charter of Serbia and Montenegro''' ({{lang-sr|Уставна повеља Србије и Црне Горе}}, ''Ustavna povelja Srbije i Crne Gore'') came into force on 4 February 2003, creating a confederacy between [[Republic of Serbia (1990–2006)|Serbia]] and [[Republic of Montenegro (1992–2006)|Montenegro]] under one government, the [[FR Yugoslavia]] amending the earlier [[1992 Yugoslav Constitution|Federal Constitution]].

