The '''Hercegovačka Gračanica monastery''' is a [[Serbian Orthodox]] [[monastery]] located in [[Trebinje]], in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]].

Largely a copy of the [[Gračanica monastery]] in [[Kosovo]], it was completed in 2000. The monastery is located above the city, on the historic Crkvina Hill, and is dedicated to the [[Virgin Mary]].<ref>[https://www.routeperfect.com/bosnia-and-herzegovina/eastern-srpska/trebinje/hercegovacka-gracanica-monastery/ Hercegovacka Gracanica Monastery, Trebinje], accessed 4 March 2017</ref>

