'''Žabljak Airport''' ([[Montenegrin language|Montenegrin]]: Аеродром Жабљак / ''Aerodrom Žabljak'') is an [[airport]] in the [[Žabljak Municipality]] in [[Montenegro]]. It is used for [[general aviation]] and cannot handle larger [[aircraft]].
== History == At the end of 1955, [[Jat Airways|JAT Yugoslav Airlines]] opened the [[Belgrade]]–[[Žabljak]] line with a [[Douglas DC-3]] airliner.
